The paper deals with the computation of entropy for compressed documents, which is a common problem in information retrieval (cs.IR) and computer vision (cs.CV). The use of run-length compression also suggests a possible connection to data structures (cs.DS) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the computational and space efficiency of the algorithms developed may be of interest to the machine learning community (cs.LG).
